# Beandown title

-- this is markdown body text, not a Beanstalk comment.

[p:
    This paragraph should be parsed as a nested Beanstalk template inside the implicit `$md` body.

    - This nested body should use Markdown list highlighting.

    [child:
        * This deeper template should also use Markdown.

        # heading to make it obvious
    ]
]

[raw_content, $raw:
    - This explicit formatter should not use Markdown highlighting.
]

[$doc:
    ## Documentation comment

    This should highlight like `$md`, including `inline code`.

    [codeblock, $code("bst"):
        import @docs {
            pages/home {render as render_home},
            pages/about {content as about_content},
        }
    ]
]

[$todo:
    This should look like ordinary Beanstalk comment text.
    It should still have a distinct todo template scope.
]

[$note:
    This should also look like ordinary Beanstalk comment text.
    It should still have a distinct note template scope.
]

Literal delimiters use string insertion: ["[literal]"]

